<p class="article-lead">Perfume batch consistency comes from controlling references and process variables, not expecting raw materials to have no natural variation.</p><p>Use approved fragrance and formula revisions, identified material lots, controlled weighing and defined mixing, resting and filtration steps. Compare appearance and odor against a retained reference under consistent conditions. Packaging consistency also requires component drawings, decoration standards and assembly settings.</p><h2>Prepare for repeat orders</h2><p>Archive the approved sample, formula revision, artwork, component specifications and production record. Review proposed supplier or material changes before purchasing. When a complaint occurs, batch and component traceability should make it possible to narrow the investigation rather than relying on memory.</p>
